class WeatherSimulator {
    int temperature;
    boolean isRaining;

    public WeatherSimulator(int temp, boolean rain) {
        this.temperature = temp;
        this.isRaining = rain;
    }

    public boolean decideToCarryUmbrella() {
        return this.isRaining && this.temperature < 25;
    }

    public boolean isSnowPossible() {
        return !this.isRaining && this.temperature <= 0;
    }
}

// Use case
WeatherSimulator todayWeather = new WeatherSimulator(10, true);
boolean needUmbrella = todayWeather.decideToCarryUmbrella();
boolean possibilityOfSnow = todayWeather.isSnowPossible();",

If it's observed that the decision to carry an umbrella is yes, can we infer if it is raining?
